      "message": "Good for this CL, but I\u0027m wondering how to deal with this in general. If we want the same results as GLSL - it seems like we should find a way to eval these undefined results? (They don\u0027t carve out an exception, and `const float x \u003d sqrt(-1.0);` compiles in WebGL just fine. Unfortunately, the GLSL grammar doesn\u0027t appear to offer NaN literals.",
